{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-03","name":"Margaret de Sherburne","nameForms":[{"lang":"und","fullText":"Margaret de Sherburne","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Margaret"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Sherburne"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Margaret De Sherborn","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1359–1390","fullLifespan":"about 1359–about 1390","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/qyn5m/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7734-118502-3737-21/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/156751634","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7734-118502-3737-21/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7734-118502-3737-21/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7753-127923-5925-73/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/181134641","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7753-127923-5925-73/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Fan Chart for Alice Sherbourne","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7743-127778-16634-30/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/180815609","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7743-127778-16634-30/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7743-127778-16634-30/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"thumbMobile","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7785-128556-4544-36/dist.png?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/182720255","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7785-128556-4544-36/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7785-128556-4544-36/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"The Coucher Book, Or Chartulary, of Whalley Abbey","description":"The Coucher Book, Or Chartulary, of Whalley Abbey\nby Whalley abbey , William Adam Hulton\n\nPublication date 1847\nPublisher Printed for the Chetham society\nCollection americana\nBook from the collections of New York Public Library\nLanguage English","date":"1847","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1359","birthPlace":{"address":"Preston, Lancashire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.76343,"longitude":-2.70304,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1390","deathPlace":{"address":"Lancashire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.81849,"longitude":-2.62573,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Removing this person from this tree effects the descendants of the following people:\nRichard Sherburne 1381–1441 L236-Y5J\nSome Descendants of (Sir) John DE SHERBURNE M.P., Knight (1303 - 1356)\nhttp://washington.ancestryregister.com/SHERBURNE00006.htm#i3210\n\nExplanation of change of name from Baylery to Sherburne -found at Geni\n\n4. Margaret SHERBURNE Heiress of Stonyhurst 5 488 (Richard DE Knight ((Sir)) 2, John DE M.P., Knight ((Sir)) 1)\n\nwas born circa 1355 in Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancaster, England and\ndied of Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancaster, England.\nMargaret married Richard BAYLEY,5 488 son of John BAYLEY and Wife of John (BAYLEY UNKNOWN, about 1377.5 488\nRichard was born before 1358 of Lancashire, England and\ndied before 1388 of Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancaster, England.\nMargaret’s marriage to Richard de Bailey provided a male Shireburne descendant. Richard was born Oct.12, 1381 and named Richard after his father. The surname however became Shireburne rather than his father’s surname de Bailey. Margaret Sherburne then conveyed all her Shireburne estates and assets to her husband Richard Bayley (descendant of Ralph the Red) to be left to their only son and heir Richard. He was however given the more predominate surname Shireburne to perpetuate the mothers family name and secure the Shireburne inheritance. Margaret’s father in law John de Bailey (descendant Mitton) was the possessor of Stonyhurst at the time. He was the grandfather of Richard Shirburne. Richard Bailey, father of Richard Shireburne never had possession of Stoneyhurst. Richard Bailey died 3 years before his father and eventually his son Richard Shireburne inherited Stonyhurst directly from his grandfather John Bailey in 1391. https://thefamilydemitton.wordpress.com/the-baileys-and-the-shireburnes-are-all-de-mittons/\n\nStonyhurt Estate:\n\nThe grounds are bounded by the River Hodder, the village of Hurst Green and Longridge Fell. The Forest of Bowland Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty overlaps in places.[2]\n\nThe earliest deed for the estate dates back to 1200 A.D. when it was known as the \"Stanihurst\".[3] It passed through the Bayley family to their descendants, the Sherburnes, before passing into the hands of Thomas Weld of Lulworth. Already possessing a large estate, he donated it to the Jesuits in 1794 as a new home for their school, of which he was an old boy when it was located at Liege.[4] A junior branch of the Sherburnes, who had earlier fled to Oxford to build and dwell in Beam Hall, subsequently emigrated to New England, where they contributed in various ways to the early history of the United States;[5] these descendants included Henry Sherburne and John Sherburne.\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stonyhurst\n\nThe Child from this marriage was:\n\n1. 6. i. Richard 'De Bayley' SHERBURNE Esq 5 68 211 488 498\nwas born 12 Oct 1381 in Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancaster, England,68 498\ndied 25 May 1441 of Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancaster, England 68 498 at age 59, and\nwas buried in Church at Mitton, Lancaster, England.","sourceList":[{"title":"Legacy NFS Source: Johanna Margaret Boteler - Published information: birth-name: Johanna Margaret Boteler","sourceType":"LEGACY","sourceUri":"M9WX-HL4"},{"title":"Margaret Bayly in entry for Margaret Bayly, \"England Births and Christenings, 1538-1975\"","sourceType":"FSREADONLY","sourceLink":"https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:J7G9-BHR","sourceUri":"3533-9YY"},{"title":"Margaret Bayley in entry for Margaret Bayley, \"England Births and Christenings, 1538-1975\"","sourceType":"IGI","sourceLink":"https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JQV8-DH8","sourceUri":"ML3C-8ZG"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1359","date":"about 1359","place":"Preston, Lancashire, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1367","date":"1367","place":"Stonyhurst, Lancashire, England","age":"8","id":"93KS-GBP"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1381","date":"12 October 1381","place":"Stoneyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancashire, England","age":"22","id":"L236-Y5J"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1390","date":"about 1390","place":"Lancashire, England","age":"31"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1352","date":"1352","place":"Lancashire, England, UK","type":"Parental"}],"parent":[{"name":"Sir Richard Sherburne","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1335–1367","birthDate":"+1335","deathDate":"+1367","age":32,"@type":"Person","identifier":"93KS-GBP","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/93KS-GBP/sir-richard-sherburne-1335-1367","published":true},{"name":"Alice Plumpton","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1335–1408","birthDate":"+1335","deathDat